{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "16", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "42", "S": "45"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa's town planning department notifies 14 proposals for zone change under 39A", "para": "The TCP department has proposed converting over 11,900 sqm of green cover and agricultural land into settlement zones across four talukas. These proposals, which include significant conversions in Bardez, Ponda, Quepem, and Salcete, are now open for public objections. Final approvals for some plots are contingent on clearances from the forest department and other authorities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/goas-town-planning-department-notifies-14-proposals-for-zone-change-under-39a/129598647?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-215948/129598647.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Noida: Residents of La Residentia renew protest over maintenance woes", "para": "Residents of La Residentia Society in Greater Noida West are protesting for the second day over alleged builder apathy and unresolved maintenance issues.  Families are demanding an urgent meeting to address problems like irregular water supply, faulty lifts, and poor upkeep. A peaceful sit-in and a 10-day camp are planned to intensify the agitation.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/la-residentia-residents-in-noida-intensify-protests-over-maintenance-issues/129598577?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-90556/129598577.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "SC gives final opportunity to Noida Authority to comply with orders on stalled sports city project", "para": "The Supreme Court has stepped in to give Noida Authority one last chance to comply with its established orders regarding the halted Noida Sports City initiatives. Following a construction freeze that took effect in January 2021, the court's recent rulings had already signaled a pathway for reconstruction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sc-gives-final-opportunity-to-noida-authority-to-comply-with-orders-on-stalled-sports-city-project/129598495?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-231086/129598495.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}